description:
&lt;p&gt;Please note this is an &lt;strong&gt;INTERNAL VACANCY ONLY for NUH employees&lt;/strong&gt;, therefore only current employees of Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust will be considered for the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We wish to appoint a motivated Midwife with a special interest in Parent Education to join our team, based at City Campus. The role will include facilitating Parent Education Workshops, with groups varying from 8 to 30 mothers and partners. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Currently due to Covid-19 restrictions we are running all our sessions on MS Teams and have been able to completely re develop the service with the hope in the future to be able to continue running both face to face and online.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role will also include ensuring the smooth running of the service from day to day administration and the assessment, planning and evaluation of workshops.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post will be 7.5 hours per week; the hours will include daytime, evening and weekend shifts and some lone working.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A full induction and an ongoing support programme will be provided.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you have any further information requirements, please contact Anthea Bowker the Parent Education Team on ext. 55178 or &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;parenteducation@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
